task.summary:
Add TooSmallMinimumPatternLengthException
* Improve documentation slightly * Add extra test case for exception
Use require instead of custom exception
Move integration test to new test class

Add GeneralizedSootNodeComparator as argument
There needs to be a default implementation of the comparator so it is possible to use this as a default argument. The one calling the pattern detector should not need to know what the nodes look like even, so we need to think about this.

Prevent out of bounds error
Use lazy evaluation. I still don't really like this method but I can't think of a way of improving it at the moment.

Integrate LengthPatternFilter
In future this could be done more elegantly but I would rather this be done after a refator.

Fix extracting suffixes
* Also ensure when end of path is reached, no longer search for path in sequence to prevent out of bounds error.

Add extra helper methods
This makes it easier to create varied integration tests.

Add extra test cases for integration
Tests seem to fail when patterns have a length of 4 however, need to look into this.

Scan all paths for suffixes
Before only the projected paths were scanned. This is not a correct implementation of the algorithm, and would not detect patterns longer than 3 nodes.

Ignore test case for duplicate patterns
The problem is that of the node pattern {1, 2, 3, 4}, every sub-pattern can be found except for {2, 3, 4}. This means that 9 patterns are found, and not 10, which is the total amount of possible sub-sequences of a sequence of length 4.

Revert to old pathContainsPattern implementation
For reasons, the new implementation only worked in test cases and not for the smoke test. It may be that this is related to the bug mentioned before that structural equality is not recursive, meaning it does not check expressions within expressions. This means that it works fine for mocks but not complex statements.
Due to there being multiple possible causes there is no way of saying this with absolute certainty, but it would perhaps be possible to retry this implementation once the new recursive structural equality is implemented.
